From: Crow Maintainers <crow@localhost>
Date: Sun, 12 Apr 2026 15:25:00 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 8/8] Unix-socket control channel for re-anchoring a running pet

Phase 3.1 added `crow_wm open pet [anchor]`; Phase 3.2 made the anchor
actually take effect at launch. But a second call while the pet was
already running was rejected ("already running"). This patch adds a
tiny Unix-socket control channel the Crow gateway can write to so
subsequent anchor calls re-position the live pet without a respawn.

Wire protocol: newline-delimited JSON.

  client → server:  {"op":"anchor","spec":{"anchor":"right"}}
  server → client:  {"ok":true,"bounds":{"x":...,"y":...}}

Other ops:
  {"op":"ping"} → {"ok":true,"pid":<electron-pid>}
  unknown op   → {"ok":false,"error":"unknown-op: <op>"}

Socket path resolution (server side):
  1. $CROW_PET_SOCKET (explicit override)
  2. $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/crow-pet.sock
  3. /tmp/crow-pet-<uid>.sock

Socket mode is set to 0600 (owner-only) — same-user trust boundary
since the Crow gateway and AppImage run as the same user. Cleaned up
on before-quit; any stale file is unlinked on startup.

Applies against: vendor/open-llm-vtuber-web @ d176e7df2366952e3bacbf12cf9a8b18a4315932
(after patches 0001-0005, 0007 — patch 0006 is empty)

